mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA&quot;&gt;The proposed development, through the
combination of the proposed and existing additions on site represent the&amp;nbsp; overdevelopment of the plot. The built form of the proposed extension will result in the exposure of a flat roof to the rear, partial closure of a gap and drop in ridge line which is detrimental to the built form, character and appearance of the host dwelling, terrace, banjo and of the wider Becontree Estate. The proposed addition would be unsympathetic and
uncharacteristic and fails to build upon the positive elements of the dwelling house and terrace, further degrading the local character, contrary to:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;- National Planning Policy Framework (MHCLG, February 2019)&lt;br&gt;- Policies 7.1, 7.4, 7.6 and 7.8 of The London Plan (March 2016)&lt;br&gt;- Policies HC1, D1 and D4 of the Draft London Plan (December 2019)&lt;br&gt;- Policies CP2 and CP3 of the Core Strategy DPD (July 2010)&lt;br&gt;- Policies BP2, BP5, BP6 and BP11 of the Borough Wide DPD (March 2011)&lt;br&gt;- Policies SP2, SPP6, DMD1, DMNE3, DMD4 and DMD6 of the Draft Local Plan (Regulation 19 Consultation version, October 2020).&lt;br&gt;- Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (February 2012)&lt;/p&gt;
